- *Oracle* has cut more than 150 jobs in its *cloud unit* in Seattle to control costs amid heavy *AI infrastructure* investments.
- The layoffs are partly due to *performance issues*, but the company is still hiring in Tennessee, where it is shifting headquarters.
- Major tech firms like *Microsoft*, *Amazon*, and *Meta* are also reducing jobs due to rising *AI costs*, with Oracle recently securing a deal with *OpenAI* for large-scale data centers.

